RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIKE NO OTHER broke out at the start and was off a step slowly, was a bit keen on the first turn, stalked the modest pace through the backstretch run, advanced three wide on the far turn, battled with CARMEL BY THE SEA to mid-stretch, disposed of the runner-up in deep stretch and kept to task late to prove best. CARMEL BY THE SEA forwardly placed into the first turn, attended to the modest early fractions, reacted slightly to RIGHT REASONS jumping a shadow to her inside entering the far turn, battled with LIKE NO OTHER to mid-stretch, could not keep pace with the winner in the final stages and outfinished RIGHT REASONS to secure the place. RIGHT REASONS assumed command into the first turn, set modest fractions through the backstretch run, jumped a shadow entering the far turn, came under pressure nearing the top of the lane, weakened in the drive and was outfinished for place, while holding safely in the end for show. SWEET TESSA was away in good order then took back off of the early fractions, well placed through the backstretch run, advanced nearing the quarter marker and lacked a late response. ROSE ROSE ROSE unhurried in the early stages, raced two wide through the backstretch run while not far back, raced three wide to the quarter marker and did not threaten in the drive.

(If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESCAPE FREE (IRE) lunged slightly at the start, was off a half-beat slowly but was away in good order, tracked the decent early pace, was roused four wide nearing the quarter marker, came within aim in mid-stretch, overtook LINGER inside of the furlong pole and kept to task while on the left lead to prevail. ELA CALIMERA MOU unhurried in the early going, steadied off of heels leaving the first turn, settled through the backstretch run, encountered traffic nearing the top of the lane, swung widest for the drive, closed well in deep stretch, could not reel in the winner and secured the place in the late stages. TIZTHEHARTOFDIXIE allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground to the quarter marker, lacked room turning into the stretch, shifted four wide for the drive, gained ground nearing the furlong pole, ran evenly in the final stages and was up in the final strides to dead heat for show. KOKO'S MOM forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent early pace, saved ground to the quarter marker, was boxed in nearing the top of the lane and continued to lack room into upper stretch, drifted out in mid-stretch, was outkicked in the final furlong and held for a share of third in the end. OAT MILK LATTE stalked the decent early pace, advanced three wide on the second turn, could not sustain that run in the stretch and faded in the late stages. LINGER showed good early speed and dictated terms in the early stages, set decent fractions while prompted to the second turn, was set down for the drive, held foes at bay to mid-stretch, could not keep pace in the final furlong and gave way. CRY ME A RUNNER was prominent into the first turn, attended to the decent fractions through the backstretch run, confronted LINGER nearing the quarter marker, lost ground leaving the second turn, came in tight and steadied off of heels in mid-stretch when KOKO'S MOM drifted out, dropped back leaving the furlong pole and could not muster a late response. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE RUNNING IN MID-STRETCH. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT WHILE CRY ME A RUNNER WAS IMPEDED BY KOKO'S MOM WHEN KOKO'S MOM DRIFTED OUT NEARING THE EIGHTH-POLE, THE INCIDENT WAS NOT ENOUGH TO COST CRY ME A RUNNER THE OPPORTUNITY OF A BETTER PLACING AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMOKIN HOT BOBBIE showed good speed leaving the break and contested the fast early fractions with SUPERSONIC FLYER, shook free of that rival and extended the lead nearing the quarter marker, drew to a clear lead in mid-stretch and kept to task in the late stages to prevail. DANIELA BELLA broke in at the start and bothered NAN ELIZABETH at the break, chased the fast early pace, raced two wide to the quarter marker, angled four wide for the drive, ran evenly to the furlong grounds, closed with a rush in deep stretch, could not reel in the winner in the final stages but outfinished ALL and secured the place. ALL content to track from the second flight in the early going, advanced from the rail on the turn, chased SMOKIN HOT BOBBIE into upper stretch, was not able to make significant headway on that rival in the drive, was outkicked in the final furlong and was outfinished for place, while holding safely in the end for show. RUNNING LUCK took back off of the fast early pace, saved ground to the quarter marker, advanced nearing mid-stretch and found her best stride late. ROLINGA chased the fast early fractions, raced two wide on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and did not offer a late rally. NAN ELIZABETH was bothered at the start by DANIELA BELLA then clipped heels with that rival and was away slowly, trailed to the turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker, swung five wide for the drive and improved position late but was unable to threaten. SUPERSONIC FLYER broke alertly, engaged with SMOKIN HOT BOBBIE in the early stages and pressed that foe through fast early fractions, kept close attendance to the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the late stages. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE START OF THE RACE. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASCENDANCY broke out a bit at the start, lagged near the back of the field for the first half mile, saving ground all the way, made up several lengths through the turn without much encouragement from the rider, split horses in mid-stretch then surged to the front under strong handling and won by a comfortable margin in the end. NAUGHTY NADINE (GB) broke out after the break bothering HARDLY MISCHIEVOUS, raced in mid-pack through the first half mile, launched a bid on the far turn, swung four wide into the stretch and rallied strongly while unable to collar the winner. WORK TO LIVE tracked behind the leading pair to the far turn, moved to challenge for the lead approaching the quarter pole, ran on well down the lane but was unable to summon another gear when needed and was outfinished by the top pair while holding third. WORTHY OF MAGIC broke outward at the break, quickly corrected and was sent for the early lead, was left alone to set the pace, led the field to the quarter pole setting solid fractions along the way, fended off some early challengers at the top of the stretch but tired with a furlong to run. BANDEENA was racing with the trailing pack early, fell back to last near the three furlong marker, saved ground through the far turn and managed to muster a mild late rally to gain a few places down the stretch. HARDLY MISCHIEVOUS squeezed back at the start when NAUGHTY NADINE came into her path after the start, was last into the first turn and content to trail the field in the early stages, made a sustained run through the far turn while four wide, and made up some ground in the stretch but was much too late. ANGEL'S ADVOCATE broke sharply, gained the rail and good position going into the first turn, was always prominent, made a bid to challenge the leader turning for home but could not find another gear and stopped in mid-stretch. SHEZARUNAWAY was outrun early and content to race near the rear of the field early, commenced a tepid rally from the three furlong pole but finished somewhat one-paced and was unable to make any progress down the stretch. BELLEO'S FOREST chased just behind the early leaders while three or four wide through the first turn, continued to race wide down the backstretch and through the far turn, began to lose ground with about three furlongs to run and was not persevered with late.
